<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-6826] Avoid range scans when forwarding values in window store aggregations</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-6826</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This is a follow-up to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-6560&quot; title=&quot;Use single-point queries than range queries for windowed aggregation operators&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-6560&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-6560&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, where we missed at least one case that should be using single point queries instead of range-scans when forwarding values during aggregation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Since a single range scan can sometimes account for 75% of aggregation cpu time, fixing this should provide some significant speedups (see attached flamegraph)&lt;/p&gt;

